Stepping out on faith usually has the potential to cost you something right?
Most of the time it's a thing called stability that is snatched away and you're left with nothing but fear to sink in. •••••
To fear something means you respect it. It has power. 
It influences your life. 
Sounds backwards I know. But think about it this way: if we fear what other people think, that means we respect them so much that their opinions matter. 
We have handed that power to someone who shouldn't have control in the first place🤔
••••
But we have a choice:
To let our faith be stronger than our fears. 
To pass the power back to the only One who truly knows what to do with it and what's best for our lives. Make sure you've placed that power in the right hands. #morningthoughts #morningvibes #morningmotivation

@Regrann from @futurenp_ -  I get this question/comment often and almost everyday. "I'm too scared to start nursing school, I feel like I'm not good enough/ it's too hard." 🗣The first step is always the most difficult. If you keep putting it off, let's be realistic, it will never happen. Stop putting off that financial aid application, stop saying you're going to start your prerequisites, stop saying you're too old and stop saying you'll call the admissions advisor tomorrow. The time to do it is now. Saying you're scared only makes your decision to start that much harder. The next few years will pass quickly regardless if you're in nursing school or still sitting there doing nothing. Nursing school takes dedication + hard work. If there's a will, then there sure as hell is a way. I'm just sayin. - #regrann
